                            <comment id="17426373" author="emilles" created="Fri, 8 Oct 2021 20:51:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Just a note, since C is a non-static inner class, it requires a reference to A in its constructor.  The code example happens to rely on the implicit null argument supplied by the compiler when a 1-parameter constructor/method is called with 0 arguments.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If the C exception type was static there would be no issue.  I&apos;ll try to fix, but it is a bit of an edge case.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17426603" author="emilles" created="Sat, 9 Oct 2021 14:33:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The example will properly produce compiler error: &quot;No enclosing instance passed in constructor call of a non-static inner class&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/groovy/commit/e22e7f5f64ad9c9900d66874ed29feb367c24176&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/groovy/commit/e22e7f5f64ad9c9900d66874ed29feb367c24176&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
